This year's library book giveaway for our open house will be virtual. Let's have some fun! Fill in the blank, If I were a book character, I would be _________.
Please, tell us why!

Five lucky winners will receive a free book!

This is how it works:
1. Like this post.
2. Comment below by filling in the blank, If I were a book character, I would be __________. Optional: Tag a friend or share this post and encourage others to come back to this post to comment to be entered!

I will place your name in the Wheel of Names app to choose the 5 winners! Giveaway ends on Sunday, September 6th by 6 PM.

The winners' books will be sent home with the student.

Good luck!

Elementary (K-4) class placement is now available through parent portal. Middle School and Junior High (5-8) placement will be updated by Friday, August 7th. We appreciate your patience.

post_text:
Today the MO Highway Patrol completed their yearly inspection of our bus fleet!

Just to offer perspective, less than half our buses passed this inspection LAST YEAR, but today they ALL passed! We are super proud of ALL our bus drivers, Amy Cogdill as the new transportation director, and Shaun Haley as our new bus, mechanic THIS YEAR! It's very satisfying to know we've been providing SAFE travel to all our students this year!

Thank you Lebanon R-3 for your partnership and assistance. We also thank you for providing the site for all our inspections!!

post_text: This week's Very Important Buckskin is Mrs. Ingrid Starnes! She is a 5th/6th grade teacher and holds a bachelor's degree in Elementary Education from MSU. post_text: This week our Very Important Buckskin goes to Mrs. Brittney Falzone and she works as a para-professional in a pre-school classroom! This is her 1st year at JEB and 1 thing she loves about her job is: "Pre-schoolers have a special way of making every day great. JEB truly feels like a family!". She also loves seeing the older students help out the younger ones. Something you might not know about her is that she is a Marine Corps wife. Her husband has been in the service for 17 years. They have 4 kids. All of her family lives in Los Angeles, California, where she is from. She loves: going to the beach year around, singing, watching her kids play sports, and watching documentaries!

post_text: This week's Very Important Buckskin is Mrs. Lacey Winfrey! This is her 10th year working at JEB. Lacey teaches K-3rd grade special education and holds a bachelor's degree from Drury University. One thing she loves about her job is the fact that she has the "best coworkers who go above and beyond to take care of each other". Something we might not know about her is that she attended JEB as a student K-8th grade and it's the only school she's ever worked at! She says: "once a Buckskin, always a Buckskin".
